abstract.text: A C union of event-specific types.

inlineContent.text: Each event monitored by Endpoint Security delivers different properties to clients. For example, a file-renaming event provides source and target paths, while a process-forking event provides the process identifier of the new child process. This C
represents each kind of event as a unique member, each with a type specific to the kind of data it contains.

abstract.text: Develop system extensions that enhance user security.
